workflow.name: Automate consent dispute handling with GPT-4o, Google Sheets, Gmail & Slack
workflow.description:
## üìò Description
This workflow automates the full lifecycle of a data-consent complaint: receiving the complaint, validating the payload, normalizing the data into a clean ticket format, storing it in a compliance sheet, generating a formal acknowledgement email for the user, and sending an internal Slack alert for the compliance team. Everything moves from intake ‚Üí classification ‚Üí communication ‚Üí escalation with zero manual handling. AI-generated messages follow DPDP-compliant tone and structure.

## ‚öôÔ∏è What This Workflow Does (Step-by-Step)

‚ñ∂Ô∏è Receive Consent Complaint (Webhook)
 Accepts a POST request containing complaint details: name, email, issue type, description, and metadata.

üîç Check Required Fields (IF)
 Validates that the complaint includes a non-empty description.
 Valid ‚Üí processed
 Invalid ‚Üí logged to a separate sheet.

üßπ Clean & Normalize Complaint Data (Code)
 Constructs a unified ticket object with:
auto-generated ticketId
normalized fields (action, email, issueType, description)
priority scoring
timestamp
source metadata
 Sets default status to Open.

üìÑ Log Invalid Complaint Records (Google Sheets)
 Stores incomplete submissions for later review.

üì• Store Complaint Ticket in Consent Dispute Sheet (Google Sheets)
 Appends the cleaned ticket into the Consent Dispute sheet including all metadata for traceability.

üß† Generate Acknowledgement Email (AI)
 Creates a DPDP-compliant support email:
mentions user name
references ticket ID
summarizes issue
sets response window (48‚Äì72 hours)
avoids legal or internal disclosures
uses formal, respectful tone

‚öôÔ∏è Configure GPT-4o ‚Äì Email Generator
 Supplies the AI model for email generation.

üìù Extract Email Subject + Body (Code)
 Splits the AI-generated email into structured fields:
subject and message.

üìß Send Acknowledgement Email to User (Gmail)
 Delivers the formatted acknowledgement directly to the user who filed the complaint.

‚öôÔ∏è Configure GPT-4o ‚Äì Slack Summary Model
 Supplies the AI model for internal Slack summary generation.

üîî Generate Slack Incident Summary (AI)
 Produces an internal, action-focused Slack message containing:
- ticket ID
- user details
- issue type
- description
- timestamp
- priority
recommended next step
No greetings, no email formatting.

üì° Slack ‚Äì Notify Compliance Team
 Sends the incident summary to the assigned Slack user or channel for quick action by compliance.

## üß© Prerequisites
Live webhook endpoint
Google Sheets OAuth (Techdome)
Gmail OAuth
Slack API credentials
Azure OpenAI GPT-4o enabled

## üí° Key Benefits
 ‚úÖ Zero-touch intake ‚Üí acknowledgement ‚Üí escalation
 ‚úÖ DPDP-compliant communication with users
 ‚úÖ Structured ticket normalization and prioritization
 ‚úÖ Instant Slack alerts for compliance action
 ‚úÖ Full audit trail in Google Sheets

## üë• Perfect For
- Data privacy teams
- Compliance & grievance redressal units
- SaaS platforms handling consent disputes
- Organizations needing DPDP-aligned automated workflows

options.systemMessage:
=You are an AI assistant working for a privacy-focused organization that follows the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act, India. 
Your job is to generate professional, empathetic, and compliant email responses related to data consent, privacy issues, and complaints.

Guidelines you MUST follow:
- Be polite, respectful, and supportive.
- Acknowledge the user's concern clearly.
- Never admit fault, wrongdoing, or share internal confidential details.
- Avoid legal promises, guarantees, or commitments.
- Do not provide technical investigation details.
- Use formal yet friendly tone.
- Mention ticket ID.
- Inform the user about next steps and expected timelines.
- Encourage them to reply if they have more details.

Response Format Rules:
- Write as a professional customer support email.
- Use short paragraphs and simple language.
- No emojis, no slang, no hype.
- End with an official polite closing.

You must output ONLY the final email message ‚Äî do NOT explain or add extra notes.

=You are an AI assistant generating internal team notifications for privacy and compliance workflows. 
The message must be formatted for Slack, short, clear, and actionable. 
Use a professional but fast-moving internal tone.
Do NOT write like an email. 
Do NOT add greetings or signatures. 
Use simple line breaks and bullet points if needed. 
Include urgency, ticket reference, issue type, and requested action. 
Do NOT add emojis unless instructed.
Output should ONLY contain the Slack message text, nothing else.

parameters.content:
## üõ°Ô∏è AI-Driven Consent Dispute Reporting & Response Workflow
Handles and tracks user complaints regarding data consent or privacy under the DPDP Act.  
Automates ticket creation, acknowledgment emails, and internal compliance notifications.

### üîπ Workflow Overview
1Ô∏è‚É£ Webhook receives consent complaint from UI  
2Ô∏è‚É£ Validates mandatory fields (name, email, description)  
3Ô∏è‚É£ Cleans and normalizes incoming data  
4Ô∏è‚É£ Generates a unique Ticket ID + assigns priority  
5Ô∏è‚É£ Stores complaint details in Google Sheets  
6Ô∏è‚É£ Sends user acknowledgement email via GPT-4o  
7Ô∏è‚É£ Notifies the compliance team on Slack  

### üîπ Tools & Integrations
- **Webhook** ‚Üí Complaint intake  
- **Azure GPT-4o** ‚Üí AI-generated emails and Slack messages  
- **Google Sheets** ‚Üí Ticket storage  
- **Gmail** ‚Üí User communication  
- **Slack** ‚Üí Team alert system

## Intake & Validation  
Webhook receives complaint payload ‚Üí Mandatory field check performed.  
Invalid submissions are logged separately in Google Sheets for audit + retries.

## Data Normalization & Ticket Creation  
- Generates unique Ticket ID  
- Assigns status and priority  
- Extracts relevant complainant information  
- Prepares clean JSON for downstream actions

## Complaint Storage & Logging  
Valid complaints ‚Üí appended to "Consent Dispute" sheet  
Invalid complaints ‚Üí appended to "Invalid Intake" sheet  
Used for compliance, tracking, reporting & audits

## Acknowledgement Email Flow  
GPT-4o drafts DPDP-compliant acknowledgement ‚Üí Subject & body parsed ‚Üí  
Delivered automatically via Gmail to complainant.

## Slack Compliance Alert  
Generates concise internal summary with ticket reference, priority & description  
‚Üí Sent to compliance team for immediate action & follow-up.

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
